==Arabic==
===Alternative spellings===
{{ARchar|انا، أنَا}}: ’ána ([[I]])</br>
{{ARchar|ـني، ـنِي}}: -nī, -ni ([[me]])</br>
{{ARchar|ـي، ـِي، ـيَ}}: -ī, -i ([[my]])

===Etymology===
{{ARchar|أنَا}} from Proto-Semitic ''*’anāk-'', ultimately Afro-Asiatic (with cognates in Berber ''nekk'', Egyptian ''ink'', Coptic ''anok'', etc.)

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ʔanaː/ [ʔɛnɛː]}}</br>
/-niː/</br>
/-iː/ (after long vowels /-ja/)

===Pronoun===
{{ARchar|أنَا}} (’ána)
#[[I]] ''(subject pronoun)''.

{{ARchar|ـنِي}} (-ni)
#[[me]] ''(enclitic object pronoun)''.

{{ARchar|ـِي}} (-i)
#[[my]] ''(enclitic possessive pronoun)''.

